13Pearson]]</small>''' |label_size=100 |marksize=7 }}\n{{Location map~ |mark = Green pog.svg | North Atlantic |lat=45.4215 |long=-75.6972 |position=right|label='''<small>[[Ottawa Macdonald-Cartier International Airport|Ottawa]]</small>''' |label_size=100 |marksize=7 }}\n}}\n|}\n\n===Cargo===\n{{Airport destination list\n<!-- -->\n| [[FedEx Express]] | [[Memphis International Airport|Memphis]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[UPS Airlines]] | [[Fort Lauderdale\u2013Hollywood International Airport|Fort Lauderdale]], [[Louisville International Airport|Louisville]], [[San Antonio International Airport|San Antonio]], [[Tampa International Airport|Tampa]] \n<!-- -->\n}}\n\n.\n\n==Statistics==\n\n===Top destinations===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 95%\" width= align=\n|+ '''Busiest domestic routes from RSW<br />(January 2019 \u2013 December 2019)'''<ref>{{cite web |title=Air Carrier Statistics (Form 41 Traffic)- U.S. Carriers |url=https://www.transtats.bts.gov/DatabaseInfo.asp?DB_ID=110&Link=0 |website=BTS, Transportation Statistics |publisher=Bureau of Transportation Statistics |accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n! Rank\n! City (Airport)\n! Passengers\n! Carriers\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Hartsfield\u2013Jackson Atlanta International Airport|Atlanta, Georgia]]\n| 575,590\n| Delta, Southwest\n|-\n| 2\n| [[O'Hare International Airport|Chicago\u2013O'Hare, Illinois]]\n| 380,050\n| American, Frontier, Spirit, United\n|-\n| 3 \n| [[Detroit Metropolitan Airport|Detroit, Michigan]]\n| 337,200\n| Delta, Frontier, Spirit\n|-\n| 4\n| [[Minneapolis/St Paul International Airport|Minneapolis/St. Paul, Minnesota]]\n| 304,260\n| Delta, Frontier, Southwest, Spirit, Sun Country\n|-\n| 5\n| [[Logan International Airport|Boston, Massachusetts]]\n| 295,200\n| Delta, JetBlue, Spirit\n|-\n| 6\n| [[Newark Liberty International Airport|Newark, New Jersey]]\n| 271,790\n| JetBlue, Spirit, United\n|-\n| 7\n| [[Charlotte Douglas International Airport|Charlotte, North Carolina]]\n| 245,860\n| American\n|-\n| 