{"title_page": "Luling, Texas", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name            = Luling, Texas\n|settlement_type          = [[City]]\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline            = Entrance to Luling City Hall IMG_8204.JPG\n|imagesize                = \n|image_caption            = Entrance to Luling City Hall\n<!-- Maps -->\n|image_map                = TXMap-doton-Luling.PNG\n|mapsize                  = 250px\n|map_caption              = Location of Luling, Texas\n|image_map1               = Caldwell County Luling.svg\n|mapsize1                 = 250px\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = {{Flagicon|USA}}United States\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_name1        = {{Flagicon|Texas}}[[Texas]]\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of counties in Texas|Counties]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Caldwell County, Texas|Caldwell]], [[Guadalupe County, Texas|Guadalupe]]\n<!-- Government -->\n|government_type          = [[Council-manager government|Council-Manager]]\n|leader_title             = [[Mayor]]\n|leader_name              = John Wells (''[[pro tempore|pro-tem]]'')\n|leader_title1            = [[City Council]]\n|leader_name1             = Jackie Campbell  <br/> John Wells <br/> John Bell <br/> James Nickells  <br/> Woody Cox\n|leader_title2            = [[City Manager]]\n|leader_name2             = Boskyler Harmoner\n|website                  = {{URL|www.cityofluling.net}}\n<!-- Area -->\n|unit_pref  =  Imperial\n|area_footnotes           = <ref name=\"Census 2010\"/>\n|area_total_km2           = 14.2\n|area_land_km2            = 14.1\n|area_water_km2           = 0.10\n|area_total_sq_mi         = \n|area_land_sq_mi          = \n|area_water_sq_mi         = \n<!-- Population -->\n|population_as_of         = 2010\n|population_footnotes     = <ref name=\"Census 2010\" /> \n|population_total         = 5411\n|population_density_km2   = 382.8\n|population_density_sq_mi = \n<!-- General information -->\n|timezone                 = [[North American Central Time Zone|Central (CST)]]\n|utc_offset               = -6\n|timezone_DST             = CDT\n|utc_offset_DST           = -5\n|elevation_footnotes      = <ref name=\"GR4\">{{cite web|url=http://geonames.usgs.gov/pls/gnispublic|title=Geographic Names Information System|accessdate=2008-01-31|publisher=[[United States Geological Survey]]}}</ref>\n|elevation_m              = 125\n|elevation_ft             = 410\n|coordinates              = {{coord|29|40|50|N|97|38|44|W|region:US_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP code]]\n|postal_code              = 78648\n|area_code                = [[Area code 830|830]] Exchange: 875\n|blank_name               = [[Federal Information Processing Standard|FIPS code]]\n|blank_info               = 48-45096\n|blank1_name              = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank1_info              = 1340735<ref name=GNIS>{{gnis|1340735|Luling}}</ref>\n|footnotes                = \n}}\n\n'''Luling''' {{IPAc-en|\u02c8|l|u\u02d0|l|\u026a|\u014b}} is a city in [[Caldwell County, Texas|Caldwell]] and [[Guadalupe County, Texas|Guadalupe]] counties, [[Texas]], United States, along the [[San Marcos River]].<ref name=GNIS/> The population, as of the 2010 census, was 5,411,<ref name=\"Census 2010\">{{cite web| url=http://factfinder2.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/G001/1600000US4845096| title=Geographic Identifiers: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (G001): Luling city, Texas| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=March 24, 2017}}{{dead link|bot=medic|date=April 2020}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> and the population was estimated at 5,954 in 2018.<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref> The town was named after a New York banker, Charles Luling. He was a personal friend of Thomas Wentworth Pierce, and provided the financing for the railroad as well the purchase of the land that became Luling.<ref>Deeds of Caldwell County, Texas. ''Galveston Newspaper'' (1874)</ref> The Caldwell County portion of Luling is part of the [[Greater Austin|Austin metropolitan area]].<ref name=OMB>{{cite web|url=http://www.whitehouse.gov/sites/default/files/omb/bulletins/2013/b13-01.pdf |title=Revised Delineations of Metropolitan Statistical Areas, Micropolitan Statistical Areas, and Combined Statistical Areas, and Guidance on Uses of the Delineations of These Areas |publisher=Office of Management and Budget |date=28 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130319014514/http://www.whitehouse.gov/sites/default/files/omb/bulletins/2013/b13-01.pdf |archivedate=19 March 2013 }}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nLuling was founded in 1874 as a railroad town<ref name=\"Texas Handbook 2\">{{cite web| last=Smyrl| first=Vivian Elizabeth| title=Luling, TX| url=https://tshaonline.org/handbook/online/articles/hjl17| work=Handbook of Texas Online| publisher=Texas State Historical Association| accessdate=14 March 2014}}</ref> and became a rowdy center for the [[Cattle drives in the United States|cattle drivers]] on the [[Chisholm Trail]]. Contempt of the law by the [[cowboy]]s helped Luling become known as the \"toughest town in Texas\". After the great cattle drives ended in the late 1880s, Luling quieted down to a town of about 500 and cotton ruled the local economy. Perhaps due to arrival of immigrants, including [[History of the Jews in Texas|a sizeable Jewish population]],{{Explain|date=September 2018}} in the late-19th century, Luling began a long, slow, period of growth, and by 1925 the population reached 1,500.<ref name=\"Ency Southern Jewish Communities\">{{cite web| title=Luling, TX| url=http://www.isjl.org/history/archive/tx/luling.html| work=Encyclopedia of Southern Jewish Communities| accessdate=14 March 2014| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140314170516/http://www.isjl.org/history/archive/tx/luling.html| archive-date=14 March 2014| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nOne of the most significant events in Luling's history was the discovery of oil by Edgar B. Davis.<ref name=\"Texas Handbook 2\" />  Davis mortgaged everything he owned to finance drilling operations around Luling. On August 9, 1922, the Rafael Rios No. 1 well struck oil at {{convert|2161|ft|m}}, producing {{convert|150|oilbbl/d|m3/d}}. To repay his loans, Davis contracted {{convert|2|Moilbbl|m3}} each to Atlantic Oil and Magnolia Oil at $.50 a barrel, plus another {{convert|2|Moilbbl|m3}} to Magnolia at $.75 per barrel.<ref name=\"Handbook of Texas\">{{cite web| title=Davis, Edgar Byram| url=https://tshaonline.org/handbook/online/articles/fda36| work=Handbook of Texas Online| publisher=Texas State Historical Association| accessdate=14 March 2014}}</ref>\n\nDavis' discovery opened up an oilfield {{convert|12|mi}} long and {{convert|2|mi|0}} wide. The economy quickly moved from the railroad and agriculture to oil. The population of the town rapidly increased to over 5,000. By 1924, the Luling Oil Field was producing over {{convert|15|Moilbbl|m3}} of oil per year, and oil formed much of Luling's economy for the next 60 years.<ref name=\"Handbook of Texas\" />\n\nAs oil grew in importance in the 1930s and 1940s, the railroads that helped form the town declined and largely pulled out of Luling.\n\n==Geography==\nLuling is located in southern Caldwell County, {{convert|47|mi}} south of Austin. The city limits extend south along [[Texas State Highway 80]] across the [[San Marcos River]] into Guadalupe County, reaching as far as [[Interstate 10]] Exit 628. Via I-10, [[San Antonio]] is {{convert|57|mi}} to the west and [[Houston]] is {{convert|141|mi}} to the east.\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], Luling has a total area of {{convert|5.50|sqmi|km2}}. {{convert|5.46|sqmi|km2}} of it is land, and {{convert|0.04|sqmi|km2}}, or 0.67%, is water.<ref name=\"Census 2010\" />\n\n===Climate===\nThe climate in this area is characterized by hot, humid summers and generally mild to cool winters.  According to the [[K\u00f6ppen Climate Classification]] system, Luling has a [[humid subtropical climate]], abbreviated \"Cfa\" on climate maps.<ref name=Climate>{{cite web|title=Luling, Texas K\u00f6ppen Climate Classification|url=http://www.weatherbase.com/weather/weather-summary.php3?s=924514&cityname=Luling%2C+Texas%2C+United+States+of+America&units=|accessdate=14 March 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|align=left\n|1880= 1114\n|1890= 1792\n|1900= 1349\n|1910= 1404\n|1920= 1502\n|1930= 5970\n|1940= 4437\n|1950= 4297\n|1960= 4412\n|1970= 4719\n|1980= 5039\n|1990= 4661\n|2000= 5080\n|2010= 5411\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=5954\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref>\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name=\"DecennialCensus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/prod/www/decennial.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|publisher=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n[[File:Luling, TX Oil Museum IMG 8193.JPG|thumb|right|The Luling Oil Museum, based on the 1922 petroleum discovery, is housed in the Chamber of Commerce office.]]\n[[File:William Johnson Cabin, Luling, TX IMG 8201.JPG|thumb|right|William Johnson [[Shotgun house|shotgun-style]] cabin in Blanche Square in Luling]] \n[[File:Stanley Theatre in Luling, TX IMG_8192.JPG|thumb|right|Though it once aired regular films, the Stanley Theatre in Luling now houses collectibles.]]\n[[File:Luling pump jack.jpg|thumb|right|One of Luling's many decorative [[pumpjack]]s]]\n\nAs of the 2010 [[census]], there were 5,411 people, 1,907 households, and 1,315 families residing in Luling. The [[population density]] was 991.6 people per square mile (382.8/km\u00b2). There were 2,115 housing units at an average density of 391.7/sq&nbsp;mi (150.0/km\u00b2). The racial makeup of the city was 70.8% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 8.5% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.4% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.5% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 16.7% [[Race (United States Census)|some other race]], and 3.1% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanics]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latinos]] of any race were 52.6% of the population.<ref name=\"Census 2010 DP\">{{cite web| url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US4845096| title=Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Census Summary File 1 (DP-1): Luling city, Texas| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=March 24, 2017| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213121634/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US4845096| archive-date=February 13, 2020| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nThere were 1,907 households, out of which 37.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 45.4% were headed by [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 17.4% had a female householder with no husband present, and 31.0% were non-families. 26.6% of all households were made up of individuals, and 14.2% were someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.75, and the average family size was 3.36.<ref name=\"Census 2010 DP\"/>\n\nIn the city, 27.3% of the population were under the age of 18, 6.3% were from 20 to 24, 24.6% from 25 to 44, 22.5% from 45 to 64, and 16.7% were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 35.5 years. For every 100 females, there were 87.9 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 85.1 males.<ref name=\"Census 2010 DP\"/>\n\nFor the period 2011\u20132015, the estimated median annual income for a household in the city was $39,157, and the median income for a family was $46,379. <!--No figure for 2015: Male full-time workers had a median income of $ versus $ for females.--> The [[per capita income]] for the city was $21,927. About 17.2% of families and 20.3% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 30.3% of those under age 18 and 14.5% of those age 65 or over.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/15_5YR/DP03/1600000US4845096| title=Selected Economic Characteristics: 2011-2015 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates (DP03): Luling city, Texas| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=March 24, 2017| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213113809/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/15_5YR/DP03/1600000US4845096| archive-date=February 13, 2020| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Cultural events==\nThe Luling [[Watermelon]] Thump is held each year during the last full weekend in June. It is a big celebration for the locals and draws many people from out of town as well. A favorite activity associated with the 'Thump' is the watermelon seed spitting contest.<ref name=\"NYT article\">{{cite news|last=Malewitz|first=Jim|title=Missing Out on the Latest Texas Oil Boom, One Town Repurposes Its Leftovers|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/28/us/missing-out-on-the-latest-texas-oil-boom-one-town-repurposes-its-leftovers.html?_r=0|accessdate=14 March 2014|newspaper=The New York Times|date=28 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nLuling is also home to Night In Old Luling, held in October. It features games, food, booths, and a scarecrow contest.\n\nSome of the oil [[pumpjack|jacks]] along the main streets of Luling are decorated with whimsical characters, such as a girl eating a watermelon.<ref name=\"NYT article\" />\n\nThe Luling Dry Tri. is an annual event held in September. It is an athletic contest comprising three consecutive events: biking 12 miles, running 3.23 miles and paddling 6 miles. A no swim triathlon (Dry Tri) where anyone may participate either solo, as a two-person tag-team or three-person relay team. The event benefits several local groups, including the Luling Police and Fire Departments, and the Luling High School Cross Country Team.<ref name=\"Dry Tri\">{{cite web|last=Ferguson|first=Sandy|title=Luling Dry Tri|url=http://lulingdrytri.com/|accessdate=14 March 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Education==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ [[Luling Independent School District]]\n|-\n! School name !! Grades taught !! Students enrolled <ref name=\"AEIS Reports\">{{cite web|title=2011-12 Academic Excellence Indicator System Campus Reports|url=http://ritter.tea.state.tx.us/perfreport/aeis/2012/campus.srch.html|publisher=Texas Education Agency|accessdate=14 March 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140215112940/http://ritter.tea.state.tx.us/perfreport/aeis/2012/campus.srch.html|archivedate=15 February 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| Rosenwald Primary ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| Head start ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 190\n|-\n| Luling Primary ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| PK-K -1 ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 231\n|-\n| Leonard Shanklin Elementary ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2 - 5 ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 310\n|-\n| Gilbert Gerdes Junior High ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 6 - 8 ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 302\n|-\n| [[Luling High School]] ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 9 - 12 ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 432\n|}\n\n==Notable people==\n* [[Michael Dorn]], actor\n* [[Marshall W. Mason]], Broadway director\n* [[Bo Burris]], NFL player\n* [[Emory Bellard]], American [[college football]] coach\n* [[Tamron Hall]], anchor for [[MSNBC]]\n* [[Obert Logan]], [[NFL]] football player for the [[Dallas Cowboys]] and [[New Orleans Saints]]\n* [[Riley Odoms]], [[NFL]] football player for the [[Denver Broncos]]\n* [[Craig Mager]], [[NFL]] football player for the Denver Broncos\n* [[Jennie Everton Clarke]], founder of the Belle Haven Orphan home\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{commons category|Luling, Texas}}\n* {{wikivoyage-inline|Luling (Texas)|Luling, Texas}}\n* [http://www.cityofluling.net/ City of Luling official website]\n* [http://www.lulingcc.org/ Luling Chamber of Commerce]\n\n{{Caldwell County, Texas}}\n{{Guadalupe County, Texas}}\n{{Greater Austin}}\n{{Texas}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities in Caldwell County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Cities in Guadalupe County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Cities in Texas]]\n[[Category:Cities in Greater Austin]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1874]]\n[[Category:1874 establishments in Texas]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name            = Luling, Texas\n|settlement_type          = [[City]]\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline            = Entrance to Luling City Hall IMG_8204.JPG\n|imagesize                = \n|image_caption            = Entrance to Luling City Hall\n<!-- Maps -->\n|image_map                = TXMap-doton-Luling.PNG\n|mapsize                  = 250px\n|map_caption              = Location of Luling, Texas\n|image_map1               = Caldwell County Luling.svg\n|mapsize1                 = 250px\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = {{Flagicon|USA}}United States\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_name1        = {{Flagicon|Texas}}[[Texas]]\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of counties in Texas|Counties]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Caldwell County, Texas|Caldwell]], [[Guadalupe County, Texas|Guadalupe]]\n<!-- Government -->\n|government_type          = [[Council-manager government|Council-Manager]]\n|leader_title             = [[Mayor]]\n|leader_name              = John Wells (''[[pro tempore|pro-tem]]'')\n|leader_title1            = [[City Council]]\n|leader_name1             = Jackie Campbell  <br/> John Wells <br/> John Bell <br/> James Nickells  <br/> Woody Cox\n|leader_title2            = [[City Manager]]\n|leader_name2             = Boskyler Harmoner\n|website                  = {{URL|www.cityofluling.net}}\n<!-- Area -->\n|unit_pref  =  Imperial\n|area_footnotes           = <ref name=\"Census 2010\"/>\n|area_total_km2           = 14.2\n|area_land_km2            = 14.1\n|area_water_km2           = 0.10\n|area_total_sq_mi         = \n|area_land_sq_mi          = \n|area_water_sq_mi         = \n<!-- Population -->\n|population_as_of         = 2010\n|population_footnotes     = <ref name=\"Census 2010\" /> \n|population_total         = 5411\n|population_density_km2   = 382.8\n|population_density_sq_mi = \n<!-- General information -->\n|timezone                 = [[North American Central Time Zone|Central (CST)]]\n|utc_offset               = -6\n|timezone_DST             = CDT\n|utc_offset_DST           = -5\n|elevation_footnotes      = <ref name=\"GR4\">{{cite web|url=http://geonames.usgs.gov/pls/gnispublic|title=Geographic Names Information System|accessdate=2008-01-31|publisher=[[United States Geological Survey]]}}</ref>\n|elevation_m              = 125\n|elevation_ft             = 410\n|coordinates              = {{coord|29|40|50|N|97|38|44|W|region:US_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP code]]\n|postal_code              = 78648\n|area_code                = [[Area code 830|830]] Exchange: 875\n|blank_name               = [[Federal Information Processing Standard|FIPS code]]\n|blank_info               = 48-45096\n|blank1_name              = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank1_info              = 1340735<ref name=GNIS>{{gnis|1340735|Luling}}</ref>\n|footnotes                = \n}}\n\n'''Luling''' {{IPAc-en|\u02c8|l|u\u02d0|l|\u026a|\u014b}} is a city in [[Caldwell County, Texas|Caldwell]] and [[Guadalupe County, Texas|Guadalupe]] counties, [[Texas]], United States, along the [[San Marcos River]].<ref name=GNIS/> The population, as of the 2010 census, was 5,411,<ref name=\"Census 2010\">{{cite web| url=http://factfinder2.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/G001/1600000US4845096| title=Geographic Identifiers: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (G001): Luling city, Texas| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=March 24, 2017}}{{dead link|bot=medic|date=April 2020}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> and the population was estimated at 5,954 in 2018.<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref> The town was named after a New York banker, Charles Luling. He was a personal friend of Thomas Wentworth Pierce, and provided the financing for the railroad as well the purchase of the land that became Luling.<ref>Deeds of Caldwell County, Texas. ''Galveston Newspaper'' (1874)</ref> The Caldwell County portion of Luling is part of the [[Greater Austin|Austin metropolitan area]].<ref name=OMB>{{cite web|url=http://www.whitehouse.gov/sites/default/files/omb/bulletins/2013/b13-01.pdf |title=Revised Delineations of Metropolitan Statistical Areas, Micropolitan Statistical Areas, and Combined Statistical Areas, and Guidance on Uses of the Delineations of These Areas |publisher=Office of Management and Budget |date=28 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130319014514/http://www.whitehouse.gov/sites/default/files/omb/bulletins/2013/b13-01.pdf |archivedate=19 March 2013 }}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nLuling was founded in 1874 as a railroad town<ref name=\"Texas Handbook 2\">{{cite web| last=Smyrl| first=Vivian Elizabeth| title=Luling, TX| url=https://tshaonline.org/handbook/online/articles/hjl17| work=Handbook of Texas Online| publisher=Texas State Historical Association| accessdate=14 March 2014}}</ref> and became a rowdy center for the [[Cattle drives in the United States|cattle drivers]] on the [[Chisholm Trail]]. Contempt of the law by the [[cowboy]]s helped Luling become known as the \"toughest town in Texas\". After the great cattle drives ended in the late 1880s, Luling quieted down to a town of about 500 and cotton ruled the local economy. Perhaps due to arrival of immigrants, including [[History of the Jews in Texas|a sizeable Jewish population]],{{Explain|date=September 2018}} in the late-19th century, Luling began a long, slow, period of growth, and by 1925 the population reached 1,500.<ref name=\"Ency Southern Jewish Communities\">{{cite web| title=Luling, TX| url=http://www.isjl.org/history/archive/tx/luling.html| work=Encyclopedia of Southern Jewish Communities| accessdate=14 March 2014| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140314170516/http://www.isjl.org/history/archive/tx/luling.html| archive-date=14 March 2014| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nOne of the most significant events in Luling's history was the discovery of oil by Edgar B. Davis.<ref name=\"Texas Handbook 2\" />  Davis mortgaged everything he owned to finance drilling operations around Luling. On August 9, 1922, the Rafael Rios No. 1 well struck oil at {{convert|2161|ft|m}}, producing {{convert|150|oilbbl/d|m3/d}}. To repay his loans, Davis contracted {{convert|2|Moilbbl|m3}} each to Atlantic Oil and Magnolia Oil at $.50 a barrel, plus another {{convert|2|Moilbbl|m3}} to Magnolia at $.75 per barrel.<ref name=\"Handbook of Texas\">{{cite web| title=Davis, Edgar Byram| url=https://tshaonline.org/handbook/online/articles/fda36| work=Handbook of Texas Online| publisher=Texas State Historical Association| accessdate=14 March 2014}}</ref>\n\nDavis' discovery opened up an oilfield {{convert|12|mi}} long and {{convert|2|mi|0}} wide. The economy quickly moved from the railroad and agriculture to oil. The population of the town rapidly increased to over 5,000. By 1924, the Luling Oil Field was producing over {{convert|15|Moilbbl|m3}} of oil per year, and oil formed much of Luling's economy for the next 60 years.<ref name=\"Handbook of Texas\" />\n\nAs oil grew in importance in the 1930s and 1940s, the railroads that helped form the town declined and largely pulled out of Luling.\n\n==Geography==\nLuling is located in southern Caldwell County, {{convert|47|mi}} south of Austin. The city limits extend south along [[Texas State Highway 80]] across the [[San Marcos River]] into Guadalupe County, reaching as far as [[Interstate 10]] Exit 628. Via I-10, [[San Antonio]] is {{convert|57|mi}} to the west and [[Houston]] is {{convert|141|mi}} to the east.\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], Luling has a total area of {{convert|5.50|sqmi|km2}}. {{convert|5.46|sqmi|km2}} of it is land, and {{convert|0.04|sqmi|km2}}, or 0.67%, is water.<ref name=\"Census 2010\" />\n\n===Climate===\nThe climate in this area is characterized by hot, humid summers and generally mild to cool winters.  According to the [[K\u00f6ppen Climate Classification]] system, Luling has a [[humid subtropical climate]], abbreviated \"Cfa\" on climate maps.<ref name=Climate>{{cite web|title=Luling, Texas K\u00f6ppen Climate Classification|url=http://www.weatherbase.com/weather/weather-summary.php3?s=924514&cityname=Luling%2C+Texas%2C+United+States+of+America&units=|accessdate=14 March 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|align=left\n|1880= 1114\n|1890= 1792\n|1900= 1349\n|1910= 1404\n|1920= 1502\n|1930= 5970\n|1940= 4437\n|1950= 4297\n|1960= 4412\n|1970= 4719\n|1980= 5039\n|1990= 4661\n|2000= 5080\n|2010= 5411\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=5954\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref>\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name=\"DecennialCensus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/prod/www/decennial.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|publisher=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n[[File:Luling, TX Oil Museum IMG 8193.JPG|thumb|right|The Luling Oil Museum, based on the 1922 petroleum discovery, is housed in the Chamber of Commerce office.]]\n[[File:William Johnson Cabin, Luling, TX IMG 8201.JPG|thumb|right|William Johnson [[Shotgun house|shotgun-style]] cabin in Blanche Square in Luling]] \n[[File:Stanley Theatre in Luling, TX IMG_8192.JPG|thumb|right|Though it once aired regular films, the Stanley Theatre in Luling now houses collectibles.]]\n[[File:Luling pump jack.jpg|thumb|right|One of Luling's many decorative [[pumpjack]]s]]\n\nAs of the 2010 [[census]], there were 5,411 people, 1,907 households, and 1,315 families residing in Luling. The [[population density]] was 991.6 people per square mile (382.8/km\u00b2). There were 2,115 housing units at an average density of 391.7/sq&nbsp;mi (150.0/km\u00b2). The racial makeup of the city was 70.8% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 8.5% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.4% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.5% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 16.7% [[Race (United States Census)|some other race]], and 3.1% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanics]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latinos]] of any race were 52.6% of the population.<ref name=\"Census 2010 DP\">{{cite web| url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US4845096| title=Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Census Summary File 1 (DP-1): Luling city, Texas| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=March 24, 2017| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213121634/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US4845096| archive-date=February 13, 2020| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nThere were 1,907 households, out of which 37.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 45.4% were headed by [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 17.4% had a female householder with no husband present, and 31.0% were non-families. 26.6% of all households were made up of individuals, and 14.2% were someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.75, and the average family size was 3.36.<ref name=\"Census 2010 DP\"/>\n\nIn the city, 27.3% of the population were under the age of 18, 6.3% were from 20 to 24, 24.6% from 25 to 44, 22.5% from 45 to 64, and 16.7% were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 35.5 years. For every 100 females, there were 87.9 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 85.1 males.<ref name=\"Census 2010 DP\"/>\n\nFor the period 2011-2015, the estimated median annual income for a household in the city was $39,157, and the median income for a family was $46,379. <!--No figure for 2015: Male full-time workers had a median income of $ versus $ for females.--> The [[per capita income]] for the city was $21,927. About 17.2% of families and 20.3% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 30.3% of those under age 18 and 14.5% of those age 65 or over.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/15_5YR/DP03/1600000US4845096| title=Selected Economic Characteristics: 2011-2015 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates (DP03): Luling city, Texas| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=March 24, 2017| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213113809/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/15_5YR/DP03/1600000US4845096| archive-date=February 13, 2020| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Cultural events==\nThe Luling [[Watermelon]] Thump is held each year during the last full weekend in June. It is a big celebration for the locals and draws many people from out of town as well. A favorite activity associated with the 'Thump' is the watermelon seed spitting contest.<ref name=\"NYT article\">{{cite news|last=Malewitz|first=Jim|title=Missing Out on the Latest Texas Oil Boom, One Town Repurposes Its Leftovers|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/28/us/missing-out-on-the-latest-texas-oil-boom-one-town-repurposes-its-leftovers.html?_r=0|accessdate=14 March 2014|newspaper=The New York Times|date=28 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nLuling is also home to Night In Old Luling, held in October. It features games, food, booths, and a scarecrow contest.\n\nSome of the oil [[pumpjack|jacks]] along the main streets of Luling are decorated with whimsical characters, such as a girl eating a watermelon.<ref name=\"NYT article\" />\n\nThe Luling Dry Tri. is an annual event held in September. It is an athletic contest comprising three consecutive events: biking 12 miles, running 3.23 miles and paddling 6 miles. A no swim triathlon (Dry Tri) where anyone may participate either solo, as a two-person tag-team or three-person relay team. The event benefits several local groups, including the Luling Police and Fire Departments, and the Luling High School Cross Country Team.<ref name=\"Dry Tri\">{{cite web|last=Ferguson|first=Sandy|title=Luling Dry Tri|url=http://lulingdrytri.com/|accessdate=14 March 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Education==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ [[Luling Independent School District]]\n|-\n! School name !! Grades taught !! Students enrolled <ref name=\"AEIS Reports\">{{cite web|title=2011-12 Academic Excellence Indicator System Campus Reports|url=http://ritter.tea.state.tx.us/perfreport/aeis/2012/campus.srch.html|publisher=Texas Education Agency|accessdate=14 March 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140215112940/http://ritter.tea.state.tx.us/perfreport/aeis/2012/campus.srch.html|archivedate=15 February 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| Rosenwald Primary ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| Head start ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 190\n|-\n| Luling Primary ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| PK-K -1 ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 231\n|-\n| Leonard Shanklin Elementary ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2 - 5 ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 310\n|-\n| Gilbert Gerdes Junior High ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 6 - 8 ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 302\n|-\n| [[Luling High School]] ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 9 - 12 ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 432\n|}\n\n==Notable people==\n* [[Michael Dorn]], actor\n* [[Marshall W. Mason]], Broadway director\n* [[Bo Burris]], NFL player\n* [[Emory Bellard]], American [[college football]] coach\n* [[Tamron Hall]], anchor for [[MSNBC]]\n* [[Obert Logan]], [[NFL]] football player for the [[Dallas Cowboys]] and [[New Orleans Saints]]\n* [[Riley Odoms]], [[NFL]] football player for the [[Denver Broncos]]\n* [[Craig Mager]], [[NFL]] football player for the Denver Broncos\n* [[Jennie Everton Clarke]], founder of the Belle Haven Orphan home\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{commons category|Luling, Texas}}\n* {{wikivoyage-inline|Luling (Texas)|Luling, Texas}}\n* [http://www.cityofluling.net/ City of Luling official website]\n* [http://www.lulingcc.org/ Luling Chamber of Commerce]\n\n{{Caldwell County, Texas}}\n{{Guadalupe County, Texas}}\n{{Greater Austin}}\n{{Texas}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities in Caldwell County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Cities in Guadalupe County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Cities in Texas]]\n[[Category:Cities in Greater Austin]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1874]]\n[[Category:1874 establishments in Texas]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDemographics:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 2011-2015 \u2192 2011\u20132015", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luling,_Texas"}
{"title_page": "2018 Cologne attack", "text_new": "[[File:K\u00f6ln Hbf, Eingang Breslauer Platz mit McDonalds und Bahnhofsapotheke-8754.jpg|thumb|Cologne Main Station one day after the attack; on the left, the McDonald's restaurant, on the far right, the pharmacy]]\nThe '''2018 Cologne attack''' was an attack and subsequent hostage-taking that occurred at [[K\u00f6ln Hauptbahnhof|the central railway station]] of [[Cologne]], [[Germany]], on 15 October 2018.\n\n==Incident==\n\nOn Monday 15 October 2018 at 12:30 German time the Syrian refugee Mohammed Abo R. entered a [[McDonald's]] fast food restaurant at [[K\u00f6ln Hauptbahnhof|the Cologne Central Station]] with a bag and a suitcase. In the restaurant he sat down at a table, drew a pistol, and spilled a flammable liquid on the floor. Shortly thereafter, he took a [[Molotov cocktail]] from his suitcase, ignited it and set the floor of the restaurant on fire.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bild.de/regional/koeln/koeln-aktuell/geiselnahme-in-hauptbahnhof-koeln-neue-pressekonferenz-57864144.bild.html|title=Geiselnahme in Hauptbahnhof K\u00f6ln: Verbranntes M\u00e4dchen muss operiert werden|website=bild.de|language=de|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sueddeutsche.de/panorama/koeln-geiselnahme-taeter-1.4172908|title=K\u00f6ln: Geiselnehmer pr\u00e4parierte Gasflaschen|last=Stegemann|first=Jana|website=S\u00fcddeutsche.de|language=de|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nThe fire ignited the clothes of a 14-year-old German girl, who ran out of the restaurant in a panic. Passersby quickly extinguished the girl's burning clothes, who, despite the rapid reaction of the passersby, suffered severe burns to her legs.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.welt.de/vermischtes/article184593536/Geiselnahme-in-Koeln-14-jaehriges-Opfer-spricht-ueber-die-Tat.html|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln: 14-j\u00e4hriges Opfer spricht \u00fcber die Tat|last=WELT|date=2018-11-28|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> Surprised by the triggered [[fire sprinkler system]], Mohammed had meanwhile fled the fast food restaurant and, armed with his gun, stormed into an adjacent pharmacy, where he took an employee hostage.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.spiegel.de/panorama/justiz/koeln-fakten-zur-geiselnahme-im-hauptbahnhof-a-1233446.html|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln: Was wir wissen - und was nicht|date=2018-10-16|work=Spiegel Online|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nAt 12:45 German time the first emergency calls reached the police.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.spiegel.de/panorama/justiz/koeln-geiselnahme-im-hauptbahnhof-zugriff-in-der-apotheke-a-1233399.html|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln: Zugriff mit zwei Blendgranaten|last=Ziegler|first=Jean-Pierre|date=2018-10-15|work=Spiegel Online|access-date=2019-10-02|last2=Eberle|first2=Lukas}}</ref> The police quickly evacuated the station and cordoned off the surrounding area.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.welt.de/vermischtes/article182111108/Polizeigrosseinsatz-in-Koeln-Geiselnehmer-soll-gedroht-haben-Frau-anzuzuenden.html|title=Polizeigro\u00dfeinsatz in K\u00f6ln: Geiselnehmer soll gedroht haben, Frau anzuz\u00fcnden|last=WELT|date=2018-10-15|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> On the phone, the perpetrator stated his demands: Free passage to [[Syria]], the release of a [[Tunisia|Tunisian]] woman and the return of his suitcase and bag from the [[McDonald's]]. He claimed to be a member of [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.express.de/koeln/ausnahmezustand-in-koeln-so-lief-das-geisel-drama-im-hauptbahnhof-ab-31442394|title=Ausnahmezustand in K\u00f6ln: So lief das Geisel-Drama im Hauptbahnhof ab|last=Meyer|first=Oliver|date=2018-10-16|website=Express.de|language=de-DE|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.derwesten.de/region/geiselnahme-koeln-hauptbahnhof-tunesierin-forderungen-is-id215576701.html|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln: Diese Dinge forderte der Geiselnehmer von der Polizei|last=derwesten.de|first=DerWesten-|date=2018-10-16|website=www.derwesten.de|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nA two hour standoff led to no peaceful solution. The perpetrator in the meanwhile had poured gasoline over his hostage, put a Molotov cocktail in her hand and a lighter in her mouth. When he tried to set her on fire, the police attacked. At 14:55 German time a [[Special Deployment Commando|SEK]] team detonated two [[Stun grenade|stun grenades]], stormed the pharmacy and shot the perpetrator, who was still armed with his pistol. Three police officers fired a total of six rounds at Mohammed, of which several hit his upper body and one hit him in the head.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.spiegel.de/plus/koeln-geiselnahme-im-hauptbahnhof-in-letzter-sekunde-a-052903ee-fe46-45e3-8696-ff506582d530|title=K\u00f6ln - Geiselnahme im Hauptbahnhof: In letzter Sekunde|last=ONLINE|first=SPIEGEL|website=SPIEGEL Plus - Das Premium-Angebot des SPIEGEL|language=de|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> The hostage was carried from the pharmacy and handed over to paramedics. Mohammed was dragged by the [[Special Deployment Commando|SEK]] Members to the square in front of the pharmacy, where [[Cardiopulmonary resuscitation|CPR]] was applied and his wounds were treated by police medics.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stuttgarter-nachrichten.de/inhalt.hauptbahnhof-koeln-geiselnehmer-unter-kontrolle-eine-frau-verletzt.1a3699fc-94a4-4947-8b1d-056962f47212.html|title=Hauptbahnhof K\u00f6ln: Geiselnehmer muss reanimiert werden \u2013 eine Frau verletzt|last=Germany|first=Stuttgarter Nachrichten, Stuttgart|website=stuttgarter-nachrichten.de|language=de|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/de/war-die-geiselnahme-in-k%C3%B6ln-ein-missgl%C3%BCckter-anschlag/a-45901561|title=War die Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln ein missgl\u00fcckter Anschlag? {{!}} DW {{!}} 15.10.2018|last=Welle (dw.com)|first=Deutsche|website=DW.COM|language=de-DE|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n== Victims ==\nDuring the incident a total of three victims were wounded, some of them seriously\n\n=== The Hostage ===\nThe hostage was treated in a clinic after the incident. She suffered a shock and a gasoline poisoning.<ref name=\"zeit.de was geschah\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.zeit.de/gesellschaft/zeitgeschehen/2018-10/koeln-hauptbahnhof-anschlag-geiselnahme-ermittlung|title=K\u00f6lner Hauptbahnhof: Was geschah in K\u00f6ln?|last=ONLINE|first=ZEIT|date=2018-10-17|work=Die Zeit|access-date=2019-10-03|language=de-DE|issn=0044-2070}}</ref> On Wednesday she was able to leave the hospital.<ref name=\"derwesten.de\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.derwesten.de/region/koeln-hauptbahnhof-geiselnahme-feuer-terror-isis-id215570009.html|title=Geiseldrama am K\u00f6lner Hauptbahnhof +++ Ermittler: \u201eDie Sprengwirkung w\u00e4re ungeheuerlich gewesen\u201c|last=derwesten.de|first=DerWesten-|date=2018-10-16|website=www.derwesten.de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref>\n\n=== Lika M. ===\nThe 14-year-old German girl Lika M., whose clothes were caught on fire by R.\u00b4s Molotov cocktail, was seriously injured. 10 percent of her skin was burned.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.derwesten.de/region/anschlag-koeln-hauptbahnhof-mcdonalds-id215828641.html|title=Lika M. (14) wurde Opfer des Anschlags im Hauptbahnhof K\u00f6ln \u2013 so geht es ihr jetzt|last=derwesten.de|first=DerWesten-|date=2018-11-19|website=www.derwesten.de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> She was treated in a children's hospital in Cologne. Eight surgeries and two skin transplants later she was able to leave the hospital in December 2018. Doctors expect her to make a full recovery.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.welt.de/vermischtes/article184593536/Geiselnahme-in-Koeln-14-jaehriges-Opfer-spricht-ueber-die-Tat.html|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln: 14-j\u00e4hriges Opfer spricht \u00fcber die Tat|last=WELT|date=2018-11-28|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref>\n\n=== Another Victim ===\nThe fire department reported another victim. This person suffered smoke inhalation, but was able to leave the hospital on the same day.<ref name=\"zeit.de was geschah\" />\n\n== Investigation ==\n\n=== Crime Scene Investigation ===\nIn the McDonald's, the bag and suitcase of the perpetrator were examined and decleared safe by [[Bomb disposal|EOD]] Operators. Further [[Molotov cocktail|Molotov cocktails]], containers with a flammable liquid and several [[Improvised explosive device|IEDs]] were found in the bags. The [[Improvised explosive device|IEDs]] were gas cartridges modified with steel balls for maximum destruction.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.waz.de/region/polizei-koeln-veroeffentlicht-ein-foto-und-bittet-um-hilfe-id215578329.html|title=Polizei zeigt nach Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln Foto von Koffer|date=2018-10-16|website=www.waz.de|language=de-DE|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tagesspiegel.de/gesellschaft/panorama/geiselnahme-von-koeln-extremes-glueck/23199364.html|title=Extremes Gl\u00fcck|website=www.tagesspiegel.de|language=de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> In the pharmacy the investigators found further containers with flammable liquid and further [[Improvised explosive device|IEDs]]. Furthermore, a airsoft pistol and an [[identity document]] were seized.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.spiegel.de/panorama/justiz/koeln-geiselnahme-polizei-schliesst-terroristischen-hintergrund-nicht-aus-a-1233437.html|title=Geiselnahme am K\u00f6lner Hauptbahnhof: Polizei schlie\u00dft terroristischen Hintergrund nicht aus|date=2018-10-15|work=Spiegel Online|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref><ref name=\"n-tv.de\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.n-tv.de/panorama/Taeter-von-Koeln-ist-identifiziert-article20674190.html|title=T\u00e4ter von K\u00f6ln ist identifiziert|last=NACHRICHTEN|first=n-tv|website=n-tv.de|language=de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref>\n\n=== Search of the Perpetrator's Apartment ===\nIn the evening of the same day, R.'s apartment was stormed and searched by the police. This happened especially in view of a possible terrorist attack and other perpetrators. Large quantities of gasoline and [[Arabic]] characters were found in the apartment. The characters are not related to [[Islamism]] or [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]].<ref name=\"n-tv.de\" /> Multiple electronic devices were seized in the apartment including two mobile phones.\n\n=== Terrorism ===\nIn the beginning terrorism was a possible motive. During the investigation kept going no evidence of relations between Mohammed Abo R. and terrorism were found. The case was ruled non terrorism related.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.zeit.de/gesellschaft/zeitgeschehen/2018-10/koeln-hauptbahnhof-geiselnahme-taeter-terroristischer-hintergrund|title=K\u00f6lner Hauptbahnhof: Geiselnehmer von K\u00f6ln hatte wohl kein islamistisches  Motiv|last=ONLINE|first=ZEIT|date=2018-10-26|work=Die Zeit|access-date=2019-10-03|language=de-DE|issn=0044-2070}}</ref>\n\n=== Mental health issues ===\nAfter terrorism was ruled out, it was determined that Mohammed suffered from mental health issues. They found that he had been in [[psychotherapy]] since 2017 and was taking medication to combat [[Depression (mood)|depression]]. He was also suffering from [[Problem gambling|gambling]] and [[Addiction|drug addiction]].<ref name=\"zeit.de Geiselnahme\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.zeit.de/gesellschaft/zeitgeschehen/2018-12/koeln-hauptbahnhof-geiselnahme-brandanschlag-islamistischer-anschlag|title=K\u00f6lner Hauptbahnhof: Geiselnahme offenbar nicht islamistisch motiviert|last=ONLINE|first=ZEIT|date=2018-12-14|work=Die Zeit|access-date=2019-10-03|language=de-DE|issn=0044-2070}}</ref>\n\n==Legal proceedings==\nPolice stated that they could not rule out a [[Terrorism|terror attack]].<ref name=\"welt\">[https://www.welt.de/vermischtes/article182111108/Polizeigrosseinsatz-Geiselnahme-im-Koelner-Hauptbahnhof-beendet-Taeter-wurde-reanimiert.html Geiselnehmer soll gedroht haben, Frau anzuz\u00fcnden], Welt.de</ref><ref name=\"faz\">[http://www.faz.net/aktuell/gesellschaft/kriminalitaet/geiselnahme-am-koelner-hauptbahnhof-beendet-15838841.html Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln k\u00f6nnte terroristischen Hintergrund haben], Frankfurter Allgemeine</ref> The Cologne prosecutor's office charged Mohammed Abo R. with two counts of [[attempted murder]], [[Battery (crime)|aggravated battery]] and [[Hostage|hostage-taking]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.welt.de/vermischtes/article182181300/Geiselnahme-in-Koeln-Taeter-identifiziert-Haftbefehl-erlassen.html|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln: T\u00e4ter identifiziert \u2013 Haftbefehl erlassen|last=WELT|date=2018-10-16|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> On 16 October 2018, the [[Public Prosecutor General (Germany)|Public Prosecutor General]] took over investigations because there were \"sufficient indications for a radical [[Islamist]] background.\"<ref name=\"ts\">[https://www.tagesschau.de/inland/koeln-geiselnahme-111.html Hinweise auf islamistisches Motiv], Tagesschau.de, 17 October 2018</ref> During the investigation no evidence for a [[Terrorism|terror]] related attack were found. In Dezember 2018 the [[Public Prosecutor General (Germany)|Public Prosecutor General]] gave the case back to the Cologne prosecutor's office.<ref name=\"zeit.de Geiselnahme\" /> The investigation is still ongoing.\n\nIn June 2019, his pre-trial detention was suspended for six months and he was transferred to a specialist neurological clinic. Experts assume that Mohammed's stay at the clinic will allow him to recover to the point where he can participate in the trial.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.focus.de/panorama/wegen-metallsplitter-in-schaedeldecke-geiselnehmer-von-koeln-aus-der-u-haft-in-klinik-verlegt_id_10831798.html|title=Geiselnehmer von K\u00f6ln aus der U-Haft in Klinik verlegt|last=Online|first=FOCUS|website=FOCUS Online|language=de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref>\n\n==Perpetrator==\nThe perpetrator was named as Mohammad Abo R.,<ref name=\"ksta\">[https://www.ksta.de/koeln/geiselnahme-in-koeln-mohammad-abo-r--war-ein-abgezockter-betrueger-31466630 Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln Mohammad Abo R. war ein abgezockter Betr\u00fcger], K\u00f6lner Stadtanzeiger, 20 October 2018</ref> a 55-year-old man of Arab, reportedly [[Syria]]n origin. He entered Europe during the peak of the [[European migrant crisis]] and was first intercepted by the authorities of the Czech Republic in early 2015. He filed an asylum application in the [[Czech Republic]] but then moved to Germany, where he filed an asylum application in March 2015. Under the [[Dublin Regulation]], the German authorities should have expelled him to the Czech Republic, but they did not do so.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rundschau-online.de/region/koeln/frist-versaeumt-geiselnehmer-vom-hauptbahnhof-haette-abgeschoben-werden-koennen-31460910|title=Frist vers\u00e4umt Geiselnehmer vom Hauptbahnhof h\u00e4tte abgeschoben werden k\u00f6nnen|last=|first=|date=2018-10-18|access-date=2018-10-19|language=de}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.novinky.cz/zahranicni/evropa/486578-syran-ktery-utocil-v-koline-nad-rynem-se-registroval-v-cesku.html|title=Sy\u0159an, kter\u00fd \u00fato\u010dil v Kol\u00edn\u011b nad R\u00fdnem, se registroval v \u010cesku |last=|first=|date=2018-10-19|access-date=2018-10-19|language=cs}}</ref> He was given permission to stay in Germany until 2021.<ref name=\"faz\" />\n\nAbo R. was known to the police. He had been charged 13 times since 2016, the charges included drug possession, theft, threat, fraud and trespassing. He was never convicted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.t-online.de/-/84622002|title=T\u00e4ter h\u00e4tte \"immensen Schaden\" verursachen k\u00f6nnen|website=www.t-online.de|language=de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref>\n\n=== Wounds ===\nMohammed was wounded by several shots, several projectiles hit him in the upper body and one projectile hit him in the head. He was carried by the [[Special Deployment Commando|SEK]] officers from the pharmacy to the square in front of the pharmacy where he was resuscitated by the officers and a female [[GSG 9|GSG9]] doctor.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/de/geiselnahme-in-k%C3%B6ln-hinweis-auf-syrischen-t%C3%A4ter/a-45893353|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln - Hinweis auf syrischen T\u00e4ter {{!}} DW {{!}} 15.10.2018|last=Welle (dw.com)|first=Deutsche|website=DW.COM|language=de-DE|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> After successful resuscitation, Mohammed was taken to the University Hospital of Cologne, where he underwent emergency surgery. He was later transferred to intensive care.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sueddeutsche.de/panorama/koeln-geiselnahme-taeter-1.4171943|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln: T\u00e4ter auf der Intensivstation|last=Zeitung|first=S\u00fcddeutsche|website=S\u00fcddeutsche.de|language=de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> On Tuesday, his condition remained critical.<ref name=\"zeit.de was geschah\" /> In a press conference on Wednesday, the police announced that the perpetrator was no longer in a life threatening condition, but was in a [[coma]].<ref name=\"derwesten.de\" />\n\nTwo months after the incident, Mohammed woke up from the [[coma]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ksta.de/koeln/geiselnahme-am-koelner-hauptbahnhof-mutmasslicher-attentaeter-ist-aus-dem-koma-erwacht-31746920|title=Geiselnahme am K\u00f6lner Hauptbahnhof: Mutma\u00dflicher Attent\u00e4ter ist aus dem Koma erwacht|last=Stinauer|first=Tim|date=2018-12-14|website=K\u00f6lner Stadt-Anzeiger|language=de-DE|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> He was later transferred to the prison hospital of North Rhine-Westphalia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.general-anzeiger-bonn.de/region/koeln-und-rheinland/koelner-geiselnehmer-in-fachklinik-verlegt_aid-44062689|title=Haft f\u00fcr halbes Jahr ausgesetzt: K\u00f6lner Geiselnehmer in Fachklinik verlegt|last=BONN|first=GA|website=GA BONN|language=de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> Due to the gunshot wounds Mohammed is paralyzed on one side and must be artificially fed, fragments of the bullet are still stuck in his skull. According to a medical report, he is not able to take part in a court trial in his current condition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ksta.de/koeln/koelner-hauptbahnhof-geiselnehmer-muss-sich-vorerst-nicht-vor-gericht-verantworten-32430864|title=K\u00f6lner Hauptbahnhof: Geiselnehmer muss sich vorerst nicht vor Gericht verantworten|last=Spilcker|first=Axel|date=2019-04-26|website=K\u00f6lner Stadt-Anzeiger|language=de-DE|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> \n\n==Reactions==\nCologne main station was completely locked down. Thousands of people, many travelers among them, gathered around the station.<ref name=\"welt\"/>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[2018 Cologne terrorist plot]] a foiled plot earlier the same year\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2018 crimes in Germany]]\n[[Category:Crime in Cologne]]\n[[Category:Hostage taking in Germany]]\n[[Category:Improvised explosive device bombings in Germany]]\n[[Category:October 2018 crimes in Europe]]\n[[Category:October 2018 events in Germany]]\n[[Category:Refugees in Germany]]\n[[Category:2010s in Cologne]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:K\u00f6ln Hbf, Eingang Breslauer Platz mit McDonalds und Bahnhofsapotheke-8754.jpg|thumb|Cologne Main Station one day after the attack; on the left, the McDonald's restaurant, on the far right, the pharmacy]]\nThe '''2018 Cologne attack''' was an attack and subsequent hostage-taking that occurred at [[K\u00f6ln Hauptbahnhof|the central railway station]] of [[Cologne]], [[Germany]], on 15 October 2018.\n\n==Incident==\n\nOn Monday 15 October 2018 at 12:30 German time the Syrian refugee Mohammed Abo R. entered a [[McDonald's]] fast food restaurant at [[K\u00f6ln Hauptbahnhof|the Cologne Central Station]] with a bag and a suitcase. In the restaurant he sat down at a table, drew a pistol, and spilled a flammable liquid on the floor. Shortly thereafter, he took a [[Molotov cocktail]] from his suitcase, ignited it and set the floor of the restaurant on fire.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bild.de/regional/koeln/koeln-aktuell/geiselnahme-in-hauptbahnhof-koeln-neue-pressekonferenz-57864144.bild.html|title=Geiselnahme in Hauptbahnhof K\u00f6ln: Verbranntes M\u00e4dchen muss operiert werden|website=bild.de|language=de|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sueddeutsche.de/panorama/koeln-geiselnahme-taeter-1.4172908|title=K\u00f6ln: Geiselnehmer pr\u00e4parierte Gasflaschen|last=Stegemann|first=Jana|website=S\u00fcddeutsche.de|language=de|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nThe fire ignited the clothes of a 14-year-old German girl, who ran out of the restaurant in a panic. Passersby quickly extinguished the girl's burning clothes, who, despite the rapid reaction of the passersby, suffered severe burns to her legs.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.welt.de/vermischtes/article184593536/Geiselnahme-in-Koeln-14-jaehriges-Opfer-spricht-ueber-die-Tat.html|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln: 14-j\u00e4hriges Opfer spricht \u00fcber die Tat|last=WELT|date=2018-11-28|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> Surprised by the triggered [[fire sprinkler system]], Mohammed had meanwhile fled the fast food restaurant and, armed with his gun, stormed into an adjacent pharmacy, where he took an employee hostage.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.spiegel.de/panorama/justiz/koeln-fakten-zur-geiselnahme-im-hauptbahnhof-a-1233446.html|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln: Was wir wissen - und was nicht|date=2018-10-16|work=Spiegel Online|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nAt 12:45 German time the first emergency calls reached the police.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.spiegel.de/panorama/justiz/koeln-geiselnahme-im-hauptbahnhof-zugriff-in-der-apotheke-a-1233399.html|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln: Zugriff mit zwei Blendgranaten|last=Ziegler|first=Jean-Pierre|date=2018-10-15|work=Spiegel Online|access-date=2019-10-02|last2=Eberle|first2=Lukas}}</ref> The police quickly evacuated the station and cordoned off the surrounding area.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.welt.de/vermischtes/article182111108/Polizeigrosseinsatz-in-Koeln-Geiselnehmer-soll-gedroht-haben-Frau-anzuzuenden.html|title=Polizeigro\u00dfeinsatz in K\u00f6ln: Geiselnehmer soll gedroht haben, Frau anzuz\u00fcnden|last=WELT|date=2018-10-15|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> On the phone, the perpetrator stated his demands: Free passage to [[Syria]], the release of a [[Tunisia|Tunisian]] woman and the return of his suitcase and bag from the [[McDonald's]]. He claimed to be a member of [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.express.de/koeln/ausnahmezustand-in-koeln-so-lief-das-geisel-drama-im-hauptbahnhof-ab-31442394|title=Ausnahmezustand in K\u00f6ln: So lief das Geisel-Drama im Hauptbahnhof ab|last=Meyer|first=Oliver|date=2018-10-16|website=Express.de|language=de-DE|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.derwesten.de/region/geiselnahme-koeln-hauptbahnhof-tunesierin-forderungen-is-id215576701.html|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln: Diese Dinge forderte der Geiselnehmer von der Polizei|last=derwesten.de|first=DerWesten-|date=2018-10-16|website=www.derwesten.de|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nA two hour standoff led to no peaceful solution. The perpetrator in the meanwhile had poured gasoline over his hostage, put a Molotov cocktail in her hand and a lighter in her mouth. When he tried to set her on fire, the police attacked. At 14:55 German time a [[Special Deployment Commando|SEK]] team detonated two [[Stun grenade|stun grenades]], stormed the pharmacy and shot the perpetrator, who was still armed with his pistol. Three police officers fired a total of six rounds at Mohammed, of which several hit his upper body and one hit him in the head.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.spiegel.de/plus/koeln-geiselnahme-im-hauptbahnhof-in-letzter-sekunde-a-052903ee-fe46-45e3-8696-ff506582d530|title=K\u00f6ln - Geiselnahme im Hauptbahnhof: In letzter Sekunde|last=ONLINE|first=SPIEGEL|website=SPIEGEL Plus - Das Premium-Angebot des SPIEGEL|language=de|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> The hostage was carried from the pharmacy and handed over to paramedics. Mohammed was dragged by the [[Special Deployment Commando|SEK]] Members to the square in front of the pharmacy, where [[Cardiopulmonary resuscitation|CPR]] was applied and his wounds were treated by police medics.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stuttgarter-nachrichten.de/inhalt.hauptbahnhof-koeln-geiselnehmer-unter-kontrolle-eine-frau-verletzt.1a3699fc-94a4-4947-8b1d-056962f47212.html|title=Hauptbahnhof K\u00f6ln: Geiselnehmer muss reanimiert werden \u2013 eine Frau verletzt|last=Germany|first=Stuttgarter Nachrichten, Stuttgart|website=stuttgarter-nachrichten.de|language=de|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/de/war-die-geiselnahme-in-k%C3%B6ln-ein-missgl%C3%BCckter-anschlag/a-45901561|title=War die Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln ein missgl\u00fcckter Anschlag? {{!}} DW {{!}} 15.10.2018|last=Welle (dw.com)|first=Deutsche|website=DW.COM|language=de-DE|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n== Victims ==\nDuring the incident a total of three victims were wounded, some of them seriously\n\n=== The Hostage ===\nThe hostage was treated in a clinic after the incident. She suffered a shock and a gasoline poisoning.<ref name=\"zeit.de was geschah\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.zeit.de/gesellschaft/zeitgeschehen/2018-10/koeln-hauptbahnhof-anschlag-geiselnahme-ermittlung|title=K\u00f6lner Hauptbahnhof: Was geschah in K\u00f6ln?|last=ONLINE|first=ZEIT|date=2018-10-17|work=Die Zeit|access-date=2019-10-03|language=de-DE|issn=0044-2070}}</ref> On Wednesday she was able to leave the hospital.<ref name=\"derwesten.de\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.derwesten.de/region/koeln-hauptbahnhof-geiselnahme-feuer-terror-isis-id215570009.html|title=Geiseldrama am K\u00f6lner Hauptbahnhof +++ Ermittler: \u201eDie Sprengwirkung w\u00e4re ungeheuerlich gewesen\u201c|last=derwesten.de|first=DerWesten-|date=2018-10-16|website=www.derwesten.de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref>\n\n=== Lika M. ===\nThe 14-year-old German girl Lika M., whose clothes were caught on fire by R.\u00b4s Molotov cocktail, was seriously injured. 10 percent of her skin was burned.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.derwesten.de/region/anschlag-koeln-hauptbahnhof-mcdonalds-id215828641.html|title=Lika M. (14) wurde Opfer des Anschlags im Hauptbahnhof K\u00f6ln \u2013 so geht es ihr jetzt|last=derwesten.de|first=DerWesten-|date=2018-11-19|website=www.derwesten.de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> She was treated in a children's hospital in Cologne. Eight surgeries and two skin transplants later she was able to leave the hospital in December 2018. Doctors expect her to make a full recovery.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.welt.de/vermischtes/article184593536/Geiselnahme-in-Koeln-14-jaehriges-Opfer-spricht-ueber-die-Tat.html|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln: 14-j\u00e4hriges Opfer spricht \u00fcber die Tat|last=WELT|date=2018-11-28|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref>\n\n=== Another Victim ===\nThe fire department reported another victim. This person suffered smoke inhalation, but was able to leave the hospital on the same day.<ref name=\"zeit.de was geschah\" />\n\n== Investigation ==\n\n=== Crime Scene Investigation ===\nIn the McDonald's, the bag and suitcase of the perpetrator were examined and decleared safe by [[Bomb disposal|EOD]] Operators. Further [[Molotov cocktail|Molotov cocktails]], containers with a flammable liquid and several [[Improvised explosive device|IEDs]] were found in the bags. The [[Improvised explosive device|IEDs]] were gas cartridges modified with steel balls for maximum destruction.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.waz.de/region/polizei-koeln-veroeffentlicht-ein-foto-und-bittet-um-hilfe-id215578329.html|title=Polizei zeigt nach Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln Foto von Koffer|date=2018-10-16|website=www.waz.de|language=de-DE|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tagesspiegel.de/gesellschaft/panorama/geiselnahme-von-koeln-extremes-glueck/23199364.html|title=Extremes Gl\u00fcck|website=www.tagesspiegel.de|language=de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> In the pharmacy the investigators found further containers with flammable liquid and further [[Improvised explosive device|IEDs]]. Furthermore, a airsoft pistol and an [[identity document]] were seized.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.spiegel.de/panorama/justiz/koeln-geiselnahme-polizei-schliesst-terroristischen-hintergrund-nicht-aus-a-1233437.html|title=Geiselnahme am K\u00f6lner Hauptbahnhof: Polizei schlie\u00dft terroristischen Hintergrund nicht aus|date=2018-10-15|work=Spiegel Online|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref><ref name=\"n-tv.de\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.n-tv.de/panorama/Taeter-von-Koeln-ist-identifiziert-article20674190.html|title=T\u00e4ter von K\u00f6ln ist identifiziert|last=NACHRICHTEN|first=n-tv|website=n-tv.de|language=de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref>\n\n=== Search of the Perpetrator's Apartment ===\nIn the evening of the same day, R.'s apartment was stormed and searched by the police. This happened especially in view of a possible terrorist attack and other perpetrators. Large quantities of gasoline and [[Arabic]] characters were found in the apartment. The characters are not related to [[Islamism]] or [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]].<ref name=\"n-tv.de\" /> Multiple electronic devices were seized in the apartment including two mobile phones.\n\n=== Terrorism ===\nIn the beginning terrorism was a possible motive. During the investigation kept going no evidence of relations between Mohammed Abo R. and terrorism were found. The case was ruled non terrorism related.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.zeit.de/gesellschaft/zeitgeschehen/2018-10/koeln-hauptbahnhof-geiselnahme-taeter-terroristischer-hintergrund|title=K\u00f6lner Hauptbahnhof: Geiselnehmer von K\u00f6ln hatte wohl kein islamistisches  Motiv|last=ONLINE|first=ZEIT|date=2018-10-26|work=Die Zeit|access-date=2019-10-03|language=de-DE|issn=0044-2070}}</ref>\n\n=== Mental health issues ===\nAfter terrorism was ruled out, it was determined that Mohammed suffered from mental health issues. They found that he had been in [[psychotherapy]] since 2017 and was taking medication to combat [[Depression (mood)|depression]]. He was also suffering from [[Problem gambling|gambling]] and [[Addiction|drug addiction]].<ref name=\"zeit.de Geiselnahme\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.zeit.de/gesellschaft/zeitgeschehen/2018-12/koeln-hauptbahnhof-geiselnahme-brandanschlag-islamistischer-anschlag|title=K\u00f6lner Hauptbahnhof: Geiselnahme offenbar nicht islamistisch motiviert|last=ONLINE|first=ZEIT|date=2018-12-14|work=Die Zeit|access-date=2019-10-03|language=de-DE|issn=0044-2070}}</ref>\n\n==Legal proceedings==\nPolice stated that they could not rule out a [[Terrorism|terror attack]].<ref name=\"welt\">[https://www.welt.de/vermischtes/article182111108/Polizeigrosseinsatz-Geiselnahme-im-Koelner-Hauptbahnhof-beendet-Taeter-wurde-reanimiert.html Geiselnehmer soll gedroht haben, Frau anzuz\u00fcnden], Welt.de</ref><ref name=\"faz\">[http://www.faz.net/aktuell/gesellschaft/kriminalitaet/geiselnahme-am-koelner-hauptbahnhof-beendet-15838841.html Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln k\u00f6nnte terroristischen Hintergrund haben], Frankfurter Allgemeine</ref> The Cologne prosecutor's office charged Mohammed Abo R. with two counts of [[attempted murder]], [[Battery (crime)|aggravated battery]] and [[Hostage|hostage-taking]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.welt.de/vermischtes/article182181300/Geiselnahme-in-Koeln-Taeter-identifiziert-Haftbefehl-erlassen.html|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln: T\u00e4ter identifiziert \u2013 Haftbefehl erlassen|last=WELT|date=2018-10-16|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> On 16 October 2018, the [[Public Prosecutor General (Germany)|Public Prosecutor General]] took over investigations because there were \"sufficient indications for a radical [[Islamist]] background.\"<ref name=\"ts\">[https://www.tagesschau.de/inland/koeln-geiselnahme-111.html Hinweise auf islamistisches Motiv], Tagesschau.de, 17 October 2018</ref> During the investigation no evidence for a [[Terrorism|terror]] related attack were found. In Dezember 2018 the [[Public Prosecutor General (Germany)|Public Prosecutor General]] gave the case back to the Cologne prosecutor's office.<ref name=\"zeit.de Geiselnahme\" /> The investigation is still ongoing.\n\nIn June 2019, his pre-trial detention was suspended for six months and he was transferred to a specialist neurological clinic. Experts assume that Mohammed's stay at the clinic will allow him to recover to the point where he can participate in the trial.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.focus.de/panorama/wegen-metallsplitter-in-schaedeldecke-geiselnehmer-von-koeln-aus-der-u-haft-in-klinik-verlegt_id_10831798.html|title=Geiselnehmer von K\u00f6ln aus der U-Haft in Klinik verlegt|last=Online|first=FOCUS|website=FOCUS Online|language=de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref>\n\n==Perpetrator==\nThe perpetrator was named as Mohammad Abo R.,<ref name=\"ksta\">[https://www.ksta.de/koeln/geiselnahme-in-koeln-mohammad-abo-r--war-ein-abgezockter-betrueger-31466630 Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln Mohammad Abo R. war ein abgezockter Betr\u00fcger], K\u00f6lner Stadtanzeiger, 20 October 2018</ref> a 55-year-old man of Arab, reportedly [[Syria]]n origin. He entered Europe during the peak of the [[European migrant crisis]] and was first intercepted by the authorities of the Czech Republic in early 2015. He filed an asylum application in the [[Czech Republic]] but then moved to Germany, where he filed an asylum application in March 2015. Under the [[Dublin Regulation]], the German authorities should have expelled him to the Czech Republic, but they did not do so.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rundschau-online.de/region/koeln/frist-versaeumt-geiselnehmer-vom-hauptbahnhof-haette-abgeschoben-werden-koennen-31460910|title=Frist vers\u00e4umt Geiselnehmer vom Hauptbahnhof h\u00e4tte abgeschoben werden k\u00f6nnen|last=|first=|date=2018-10-18|access-date=2018-10-19|language=de}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.novinky.cz/zahranicni/evropa/486578-syran-ktery-utocil-v-koline-nad-rynem-se-registroval-v-cesku.html|title=Sy\u0159an, kter\u00fd \u00fato\u010dil v Kol\u00edn\u011b nad R\u00fdnem, se registroval v \u010cesku |last=|first=|date=2018-10-19|access-date=2018-10-19|language=cs}}</ref> He was given permission to stay in Germany until 2021.<ref name=\"faz\" />\n\nAbo R. was known to the police. He had been charged 13 times since 2016, the charges included drug possession, theft, threat, fraud and trespassing. He was never convicted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.t-online.de/-/84622002|title=T\u00e4ter h\u00e4tte \"immensen Schaden\" verursachen k\u00f6nnen|website=www.t-online.de|language=de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref>\n\n=== Wounds ===\nMohammed was wounded by several shots, several projectiles hit him in the upper body and one projectile hit him in the head. He was carried by the [[Special Deployment Commando|SEK]] officers from the pharmacy to the square in front of the pharmacy where he was resuscitated by the officers and a female [[GSG 9|GSG9]] doctor.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/de/geiselnahme-in-k%C3%B6ln-hinweis-auf-syrischen-t%C3%A4ter/a-45893353|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln - Hinweis auf syrischen T\u00e4ter {{!}} DW {{!}} 15.10.2018|last=Welle (dw.com)|first=Deutsche|website=DW.COM|language=de-DE|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> After successful resuscitation, Mohammed was taken to the University Hospital of Cologne, where he underwent emergency surgery. He was later transferred to intensive care.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sueddeutsche.de/panorama/koeln-geiselnahme-taeter-1.4171943|title=Geiselnahme in K\u00f6ln: T\u00e4ter auf der Intensivstation|last=Zeitung|first=S\u00fcddeutsche|website=S\u00fcddeutsche.de|language=de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> On Tuesday, his condition remained critical.<ref name=\"zeit.de was geschah\" /> In a press conference on Wednesday, the police announced that the perpetrator was no longer in a life threatening condition, but was in a [[coma]].<ref name=\"derwesten.de\" />\n\nTwo months after the incident, Mohammed woke up from the [[coma]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ksta.de/koeln/geiselnahme-am-koelner-hauptbahnhof-mutmasslicher-attentaeter-ist-aus-dem-koma-erwacht-31746920|title=Geiselnahme am K\u00f6lner Hauptbahnhof: Mutma\u00dflicher Attent\u00e4ter ist aus dem Koma erwacht|last=Stinauer|first=Tim|date=2018-12-14|website=K\u00f6lner Stadt-Anzeiger|language=de-DE|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> He was later transferred to the prison hospital of North Rhine-Westphalia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.general-anzeiger-bonn.de/region/koeln-und-rheinland/koelner-geiselnehmer-in-fachklinik-verlegt_aid-44062689|title=Haft f\u00fcr halbes Jahr ausgesetzt: K\u00f6lner Geiselnehmer in Fachklinik verlegt|last=BONN|first=GA|website=GA BONN|language=de|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> Due to the gunshot wounds Mohammed is paralyzed on one side and must be artificially fed, fragments of the bullet are still stuck in his skull. According to a medical report, he is not able to take part in a court trial in his current condition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ksta.de/koeln/koelner-hauptbahnhof-geiselnehmer-muss-sich-vorerst-nicht-vor-gericht-verantworten-32430864|title=K\u00f6lner Hauptbahnhof: Geiselnehmer muss sich vorerst nicht vor Gericht verantworten|last=Spilcker|first=Axel|date=2019-04-26|website=K\u00f6lner Stadt-Anzeiger|language=de-DE|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref> \n\n==Reactions==\nCologne main station was completely locked down. Thousands of people, many travelers among them, gathered around the station.<ref name=\"welt\"/>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[2018 Cologne terrorist plot]] a foiled plot earlier the same year\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2018 crimes in Germany]]\n[[Category:Crime in North Rhine-Westphalia]]\n[[Category:Hostage taking in Germany]]\n[[Category:Improvised explosive device bombings in Germany]]\n[[Category:October 2018 crimes in Europe]]\n[[Category:October 2018 events in Germany]]\n[[Category:Refugees in Germany]]\n[[Category:2010s in Cologne]]\n", "name_user": "Timmaexx", "label": "safe", "comment": "Precised the Category", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2018_Cologne_attack"}
